HEADWORD: Girdlestead
<hw>Gir"dle*stead</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Girdle</ets> + <ets>stead</ets> place.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That part of the body where the girdle is
worn.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sheathed, beneath his <qex>girdlestead</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The lap.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There fell a flower into her <qex>girdlestead</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Swinburne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gire</ent>⟦br⟧
